{"name": "dissect-cim", "metadata": {"name": "dissect.cim", "version": "3.10", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: Information Technology", "License :: OSI Approved", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Internet :: Log Analysis", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Information Analysis", "Topic :: Security", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": null, "license": "Affero General Public License v3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["dissect.cstruct", "dissect.util"], "summary": "A Dissect module implementing a parser for the Windows Common Information Model (CIM) database, used in the Windows operating system", "upload_time": 1719823050}, "documentation": ["# dissect.cim\n\nA Dissect module implementing a parser for the Windows Common Information Model (CIM) database, used in the Windows\noperating system. For more information, please see [the\ndocumentation](https://docs.dissect.tools/en/latest/projects/dissect.cim/index.html).\n\n## Requirements\n\nThis project is part of the Dissect framework and requires Python.\n\nInformation on the supported Python versions can be found in the Getting Started section of [the documentation](https://docs.dissect.tools/en/latest/index.html#getting-started).\n\n## Installation\n\n`dissect.cim` is available on [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/dissect.cim/).\n\n```bash\npip install dissect.cim\n```\n\nThis module is also automatically installed if you install the `dissect` package.\n\n## Build and test instructions\n\nThis project uses `tox` to build source and wheel distributions. Run the following command from the root folder to build\nthese:\n\n```bash\ntox -e build\n```\n\nThe build artifacts can be found in the `dist/` directory.\n\n`tox` is also used to run linting and unit tests in a self-contained environment. To run both linting and unit tests\nusing the default installed Python version, run:\n\n```bash\ntox\n```\n\nFor a more elaborate explanation on how to build and test the project, please see [the\ndocumentation](https://docs.dissect.tools/en/latest/contributing/tooling.html).\n\n## Contributing\n\nThe Dissect project encourages any contribution to the codebase. To make your contribution fit into the project, please\nrefer to [the development guide](https://docs.dissect.tools/en/latest/contributing/developing.html).\n\n## Copyright and license\n\nDissect is released as open source by Fox-IT (<https://www.fox-it.com>) part of NCC Group Plc\n(<https://www.nccgroup.com>).\n\nDeveloped by the Dissect Team (<dissect@fox-it.com>) and made available at <https://github.com/fox-it/dissect>.\n\nLicense terms: AGPL3 (<https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html>). For more information, see the LICENSE file.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "dissect.cim.mappings", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cim", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fh", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "k", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping._generate_reverse_map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping.get_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "logical_num", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.Mapping.reverse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "physical_num", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Provides forward and reverse lookup of physical and logical pages."]}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.MappingEntry", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.MappingEntry.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "entry", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.mappings.MappingEntry.is_mapped", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dissect.cim.utils.is_xp_mapping", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "h", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.utils.find_current_mapping", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mappings", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.utils.parse_object_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "object_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ns", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["given a textual query string, parse it into an object path that we can query.\n\nsupported schemas:\n    cimv2 --> namespace\n    //./root/cimv2 --> namespace\n    //HOSTNAME/root/cimv2 --> namespace\n    winmgmts://./root/cimv2 --> namespace\n    Win32_Service --> class\n    //./root/cimv2:Win32_Service --> class\n    Win32_Service.Name='Beep' --> instance\n    //./root/cimv2:Win32_Service.Name=\"Beep\" --> instance\n\nwe'd like to support this, but can't differentiate this\n    from a class:\n    //./root/cimv2/Win32_Service --> class\n\nArgs:\n    object_path (str): the textual query string.\n    ns:\n\nReturns:\n    ObjectPath: a path we can use to query."]}], "variables": [{"name": "dissect.cim.utils.ObjectPath", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.cim_def", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.c_cim", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.DATA_PAGE_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.INDEX_PAGE_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.INDEX_PAGE_INVALID", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.INDEX_PAGE_INVALID2", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.MAPPING_PAGE_ID_MASK", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.MAPPING_PAGE_UNAVAIL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.MAPPING_FILE_CLEAN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.UNMAPPED_PAGE_VALUE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.ROOT_NAMESPACE_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.SYSTEM_NAMESPACE_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.NAMESPACE_CLASS_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.ARRAY_STATES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.BOOLEAN_STATES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.DYNPROPS_STATES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.BUILTIN_QUALIFIERS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.BUILTIN_PROPERTIES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dissect.cim.c_cim.CIM_TYPES", "type": null, "documentation":